Wesley Mini was shot and killed about earlier this month near his home in Thembalethu. CAPE TOWN - A murdered George taxi boss is being laid to rest today in Queenstown.Wesley Mini was shot and killed about earlier this month near his home in Thembalethu, a township in George, while on his way home from a meeting.Some taxi drivers believe Mini was killed to disrupt a mediation process between taxi drivers and provincial government over the Go George bus service. In August, taxi operators demonstrated over what they claim is a lack of proper consultation in the implementation of the Go George bus rapid transit system.UNCEDO Taxi Association spokesperson Cornelius Esau said, We have been informed by the police that they are very close to a breakthrough in the case and we hope by next week there will be a definite arrest. No arrests have yet been made.